==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pharmacopœia
<hw>Phar`ma*co*p⟦oe⟧"ia</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
Gr. <grk>farmakopoii:`a</grk> the preparation of medicines;
<grk>fa`rmakon</grk> medicine + <grk>poiei^n</grk> to make.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A book or treatise describing the drugs, preparations,
etc., used in medicine; especially, one that is issued by official
authority and considered as an authoritative standard.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A chemical laboratory.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pharmacopolist</ent>⟦br⟧
